Component Responsibilities

Wallets

The Wallets module tracks treasury addresses across supported blockchains.

Responsibilities:

Monitor wallet balances
Track inflows and outflows
Classify wallets by purpose
Detect abnormal movements
Support read-only treasury visibility
Prepare future multisig integration
Market Data

The Market Data module provides external financial and on-chain information.

Responsibilities:

Fetch token prices
Monitor liquidity depth
Track volatility
Analyze yield opportunities
Collect macro and market indicators
Provide normalized data to the Portfolio Manager
Risk Engine

The Risk Engine evaluates the current treasury exposure.

Responsibilities:

Analyze asset concentration
Monitor stablecoin exposure
Detect volatility risk
Evaluate liquidity risk
Score counterparty exposure
Generate risk alerts
Support scenario simulations
Portfolio Manager

The Portfolio Manager is the central decision layer of the system.

Responsibilities:

Combine wallet data, market data, and risk signals
Evaluate portfolio allocation
Generate treasury recommendations
Produce reports
Decide whether a rebalance should be suggested
Send proposed actions to the Execution Layer
Execution Layer

The Execution Layer prepares possible treasury actions but does not execute them automatically by default.

Responsibilities:

Prepare swap recommendations
Simulate rebalancing
Estimate gas costs
Suggest bridges when needed
Generate approval-ready transaction plans
Support future multisig workflows
Data Flow
sequenceDiagram
